          "content": "üö¶ Essential Traffic Rules for Car Drivers\\n\\n1. SPEED LIMITS\\n‚Ä¢ Inside Kathmandu Valley: 40 km/h\\n‚Ä¢ City roads: 50 km/h\\n‚Ä¢ Highways: 80 km/h\\n‚Ä¢ Near schools: 20 km/h\\n‚Ä¢ Hospital zones: 25 km/h\\n\\n2. SEATBELT RULES\\n‚Ä¢ Mandatory for driver and front passenger\\n‚Ä¢ Children under 5 in child seat\\n‚Ä¢ Fine for violation: Rs. 500\\n\\n3. LANE DISCIPLINE\\n‚Ä¢ Keep left unless overtaking\\n‚Ä¢ Overtake from right side only\\n‚Ä¢ Use indicators 30m before turning\\n‚Ä¢ No zigzag driving\\n\\n4. TRAFFIC SIGNALS\\n‚Ä¢ Red: Complete stop behind line\\n‚Ä¢ Yellow: Stop if safe to do so\\n‚Ä¢ Green: Proceed with caution\\n‚Ä¢ Flashing red: Treat as stop sign\\n‚Ä¢ Flashing yellow: Proceed with caution\\n\\n5. RIGHT OF WAY\\n‚Ä¢ Emergency vehicles always have priority\\n‚Ä¢ Give way to traffic from right at unmarked intersections\\n‚Ä¢ Pedestrians at zebra crossings\\n‚Ä¢ Uphill vehicles on narrow mountain roads\\n‚Ä¢ Buses pulling out from stops\\n\\n6. OVERTAKING RULES\\n‚Ä¢ Only from right side\\n‚Ä¢ Not at turns or intersections\\n‚Ä¢ Not on narrow roads\\n‚Ä¢ Ensure clear road ahead\\n‚Ä¢ Use horn to warn\\n‚Ä¢ Complete overtaking quickly\\n\\n7. PARKING REGULATIONS\\n‚Ä¢ No parking within 6 meters of intersection\\n‚Ä¢ No parking on pedestrian crossings\\n‚Ä¢ No parking in no-parking zones\\n‚Ä¢ Use parking lights at night\\n‚Ä¢ Park in direction of traffic\\n\\n8. PROHIBITED ACTIONS\\n‚Ä¢ Using mobile phone while driving (Fine: Rs. 1000)\\n‚Ä¢ Driving under influence (Fine: Rs. 10,000 + jail)\\n‚Ä¢ Racing on public roads\\n‚Ä¢ Playing loud music\\n‚Ä¢ Tinted glass beyond legal limit\\n‚Ä¢ Honking in silence zones\\n\\n9. DOCUMENTS TO CARRY\\n‚Ä¢ Valid driving license\\n‚Ä¢ Vehicle registration (bluebook)\\n‚Ä¢ Insurance certificate\\n‚Ä¢ Pollution Under Control (PUC) certificate\\n‚Ä¢ Tax payment receipt\\n\\n10. NIGHT DRIVING\\n‚Ä¢ Use dipped headlights in traffic\\n‚Ä¢ Full beam only on empty roads\\n‚Ä¢ Dim lights when vehicle approaches\\n‚Ä¢ Ensure all lights working\\n\\n11. MONSOON DRIVING\\n‚Ä¢ Reduce speed on wet roads\\n‚Ä¢ Increase following distance\\n‚Ä¢ Use wipers and defogger\\n‚Ä¢ Avoid puddles at speed\\n‚Ä¢ Be extra cautious\\n\\n12. PEDESTRIAN SAFETY\\n‚Ä¢ Always give way at crossings\\n‚Ä¢ Slow down in crowded areas\\n‚Ä¢ Be alert near schools\\n‚Ä¢ Watch for children\\n\\n13. HORN USAGE\\n‚Ä¢ Only for warning\\n‚Ä¢ Not in silence zones\\n‚Ä¢ Not from 10 PM to 6 AM in residential areas\\n\\n14. ACCIDENT PROCEDURE\\n‚Ä¢ Stop immediately\\n‚Ä¢ Call police (100) and ambulance (102)\\n‚Ä¢ Help injured if possible\\n‚Ä¢ Don't move vehicle (unless blocking traffic)\\n‚Ä¢ Exchange information with other party\\n‚Ä¢ Take photos for insurance\\n\\n15. MAJOR PENALTIES\\n‚Ä¢ No license: Rs. 2000 + vehicle impounded\\n‚Ä¢ Drunk driving: Rs. 10,000 + jail (up to 6 months)\\n‚Ä¢ No insurance: Rs. 1000\\n‚Ä¢ No seatbelt: Rs. 500\\n‚Ä¢ Jumping red light: Rs. 1000\\n‚Ä¢ Wrong side driving: Rs. 2000\\n‚Ä¢ Overspeeding: Rs. 1000-5000\\n‚Ä¢ No helmet (bike): Rs. 500\\n‚Ä¢ Using phone: Rs. 1000\\n\\nRemember: Traffic rules are for your safety and others. Always drive defensively and courteously!"
